args:
Nadine invites Nefaria to accompany her to a
festival held by the dunefolk, descendants of
the revenant queen's subjects. Not wanting to
cause a scene, Nefaria borrows clothes from
Nadine in order to hide her identity and sets off
with her incognito.
Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor Nefaria and Nadine's adventurer stories.
(Ah... My consciousness fades...\nThe end draws nigh...)
Aaah! *heave* *pant* *pant*\n...It was a dream. No more.
(Why would slumber visit this chimera\nof my final moments upon me now,\nso long hence?)

And yet, no such person was present at the
moment of my death. Whoever it was who
invaded my dreams, they named me
Queen of the Sandreach...
Ohmigosh, Ria! Bombshell news!\nIt's for seriously the G.O.A.T.M.!
I give you good day, Nadine.\nBut pray, what is...ï¼‚goat emï¼‚?
Greatest of all this morning! Duh-doy!\nAnyway, check this...
It's almost festival time back home!\nI, like, COMPLETELY blanked on it till now.
They've been holding this rager since\npretty much forever and a half ago, soâ€”
Whaaat?! Ohmigosh, girl, did you just\nremember your past?!
Naught save my kingdom's name;\nthe rest eludes me still.
Aw, boo. But still, that's progress.
Indeedâ€”and I shall continue to seek my\nlost recollections, one after the next.
And you KNOW I'm gonna help!
I would fain accept no less; it was your\nurging that bestirred me to undertake\nthe matter, after all.
Hee hee! Guilty as charged. But yeah,\nlet's put in an appearance at the big fest.\nIt'll be lit!
Prithee hold a moment. Where does\nyour homeland now stand?
Did you not afore say it held\nno fixed location?
Yup! Us dunefolk rock that nomad lifestyle,\nso we're always on the move in search of\nthe next great spot or whatever.
But right now, the whole squad\nis right in South Grastaea!

So wanna hit the festival and meet some
other dunefolk? I mean, it's LITERALLY
just down the road. ...Okay, not literally.
More like down a couple roads.
The thought is not without appeal.
Heck yeah! Who's got two thumbs and a\nbuncha fingers and just scored a date to\nthe festival? THIS GIRL!
You presume overmuch, Nadine.\nI have not yet plighted my attendance.
Whaaat? Why not? I mean, you SAID\nyou're interested, so let's do this thing!

Pray pore on this a moment. The dead do
not rise again as a matter of course: If I
were to appear anew before my subjects,
it would likely cause them much grief.
Aw, they'll be fine! They wouldn't have\nsent me looking for you if they didn't think\nyou'd come back in the first place, right?
Okay, so what I'm hearing is that you're\ncool with this so long as they don't know\nyou're the queen lady or whatever, yeah?
Well then, I'll just work my stylist magic\nand get you the hook-up on a new steez!
By ï¼‚steez,ï¼‚ you speak of a disguise?
Yeah! I mean, I ADORE your look, girl,\nbut wearing clothes from a million years\nago is pretty much a huge spoiler.
So you can just wear MY clothes and I'll\ntell everyone you're my new BFF!
Next stop, Nadine's room! Choo choooo!
Ria, I can't. I can't even REMOTELY.\nI'm trying, but the struggle is so real.
*sigh* I warned you such trappings\nwould ill suit me.
What?! No! I mean I can't in a GOOD way!
Ria, that look is hot fire. You're serving\nstraight-up disguise realness!
YOU LOOK ADORABLE! I gotta get a snap!\nCan I? Pleeeease?
You truly believe this simple change in\ngarb enough to dissemble me?

Well, not if you talk all fancy-pants and
use words like ï¼‚dissembleï¼‚ and ï¼‚garbï¼‚
and ï¼‚thou art thy maiden's hedgerowï¼‚
or whatever it is you say all the time.
I'm just saying the way you talk is\nsuuuuper queen-y.
Changing the outside is a solid start, \nbut if you change the whole PACKAGE,\nit'll be a done deal!
You speak soothâ€”and yet, I know not\nwhether such a feat is even possible.
Well, for one, you can stop saying ï¼‚sooth.ï¼‚
Here, I'll totally coach you or whatever.\nDon't worry, we'll start off easy...
Ohmigosh, that was PERFECT! ...Except\nyou said ï¼‚beefs.ï¼‚ But whatevs, we'll fix\nthat in post. This is totally gonna work!
Truly! And now that THAT'S solved...
(What madness have I loosed upon\nmyself this day...?)
